results.name: Number of antichains in divisor lattice D(n).
comment: The divisor lattice D(n) is the lattice of the divisors of the natural number n.
The empty set is counted as an antichain in D(n).
a(n) = gamma(n+1) where gamma is degree of cardinal completeness of Łukasiewicz n-valued logic. - _Artur Jasinski_, Mar 01 2010
reference: Alexander S. Karpenko, Lukasiewicz's Logics and Prime Numbers, Luniver Press, Beckington, 2006. See Table I p. 113.
link: Arkadiusz Wesolowski, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..990
